lenders.loan_because:
REASON FOR SEEKING ASSISTANCE 
I thought of raising fun to buy a Taxi and commercialize it to generate income for my family. I would be the driver after officially work. The income generated is intended to be spent on the family in the areas of mostly Health and education. The Taxi if available will be used to transport passengers around rural and urban communities within the region and district we live at. Transport, is a high demand in The Gambia and it’s therefore a basic need for the people in The Gambia. Sometimes even private car owners don’t have money to buy fuel for their cars for daily use and they end up parking them and board commercial buses and Taxies or use their cars as taxi after work to generate extra money for themselves.
lenders.occupational_info:
I am a 31 year old Gambian living in a rural village called Mandinaba. Although it is now considered to be the divide between rural and urban Gambia, it is also a Transit point for travellers from Senegal, Guinea Bissau and Rural - Urban Gambia in particular.
However, I lived in an extended family with my brother and his wife, sister, mother and my wife. I have one daughter who is 8months old. My brother has 5 children, one girl and four boys. We all share the same household. I am the only member of my household who is currently working on a monthly role; with monthly earnings of up to $75 per month. I work as an IT teacher at a Senior Secondary School 7 to 8 kilometres from my home. I sometimes take up contracts in my specialized area of IT; (repairs and maintenance, configuring, installation etc) and at least get up to $5 to $10 per computer depending on the type of work. But this is rarely available. 
My brother and his children usually embark on farming and some of the women like my sister and my brothers’ wife does gardening. Sometimes depending on the type of season; they do petty trading on fruit trees, farm crops, etc. All the income generated is geared towards uplifting of the household. My brother, outside the rainy season does petty contracts to get some money for the household as well. Our children are all attending school; except 2, my 8months daughter and my brother first daughter who is 19, is a dropout due to financial reasons.
